with a straw doll collection!

18:59.591 --> 19:02.827
You guys, this was not our fault!
It was an accident!

19:02.828 --> 19:04.745
Actually, the official
citation from the County Clerk

19:04.746 --> 19:06.743
did say something like
this could happen.

19:06.744 --> 19:08.022
Something like this did happen!

19:08.023 --> 19:10.380
Could this day get any worse?!

19:33.837 --> 19:36.873
Dude, we can't use paper towels...
there is blood everywhere!

19:36.874 --> 19:37.792
Well, what then?!

19:37.793 --> 19:39.092
Got it!

19:42.688 --> 19:45.784
Charlie! Get something to wrap him in
and I'll pull around the car!

19:45.785 --> 19:46.883
Vacuum, Ned.

19:46.884 --> 19:48.463
Aw, man.

20:14.936 --> 20:18.173
Come on. Come on!

20:20.330 --> 20:22.108
Yes!

20:24.466 --> 20:25.365
Walter!

20:25.366 --> 20:28.461
Those Harkers are up to something...
I know it!

20:28.462 --> 20:31.260
Dammit, Mavis! Leave them boys be.

20:32.398 --> 20:36.654
Get over there now
or I'll smother you in your sleep!

20:36.894 --> 20:38.493
You would.

20:44.206 --> 20:45.664
Whoa.

20:45.665 --> 20:48.121
It looks pretty damn clean in here.
Good work.

20:48.122 --> 20:49.580
Well, you know.

20:49.581 --> 20:51.240
Let's turn him over!

20:54.056 --> 20:55.894
I didn't know rigor
mortis set in so fast.

20:55.895 --> 20:56.654
It doesn't.

20:56.655 --> 20:58.671
Well he was on a lot of drugs.

20:58.672 --> 21:01.288
Man, if you could show
this to kids, and say look...

21:01.289 --> 21:02.888
Look what can happen!

21:03.427 --> 21:05.044
Hey, hey, Walter!

21:05.045 --> 21:09.260
Sorry to bother you, but you know
that soul-sucking succubus of a wife...?

21:09.261 --> 21:12.397
She literally threatened to kill me
if I didn't come over and find out

21:12.398 --> 21:14.175
what's going on with all the ruckus.

21:14.176 --> 21:15.933
Just sprucing the place up.

21:15.934 --> 21:17.741
You know I heard about what happened.

21:17.933 --> 21:19.090
Yeah. The County Clerk.

21:19.091 --> 21:20.549
Yeah! Yeah, yeah...

21:20.550 --> 21:21.768
You need any help?

21:21.769 --> 21:23.488
No, no, no... we're fine.

21:24.626 --> 21:27.202
That's a damn shame about
your father's passing.

21:27.203 --> 21:30.379
He did such a fine job of
raising you kiddos on his own.

21:30.380 --> 21:33.098
I never knew your mother,
but she was a...

21:35.295 --> 21:37.094
handsome woman.

21:38.132 --> 21:39.610
Yeah.

21:39.611 --> 21:41.208
How you boys holding up?

21:41.209 --> 21:42.427
We're fine!

21:42.428 --> 21:46.924
Well... if you need anything,
I'll probably be murdered by my wife.

21:47.403 --> 21:49.002
Goodnight.

21:50.340 --> 21:51.398
Ned.

21:51.399 --> 21:52.998
Walter.

22:24.706 --> 22:27.562
Let's dump it right here. Come on.

22:37.952 --> 22:39.631
Where do you think it goes?

22:40.630 --> 22:42.567
Probably Lake Superior.

22:42.768 --> 22:43.727
This isn't going to work.

22:43.728 --> 22:46.203
Charlie... it's gonna work!

22:46.204 --> 22:49.222
I saw it on an episode
of Unsolved Mysteries.

22:50.540 --> 22:52.017
Hello...

22:52.018 --> 22:53.957
'Unsolved.'

22:54.436 --> 22:57.632
At least we know the body is
gonna be far away from here. Come on.

23:13.916 --> 23:15.815
Hey, Kip?

23:16.014 --> 23:17.713
Yeah, Denny?

23:20.610 --> 23:22.367
Found a body.

23:29.661 --> 23:31.839
You guys are up early.

23:31.898 --> 23:34.655
Or you never went to bed.
Long night?

23:34.656 --> 23:37.492
How... how... how was your night?

23:37.493 --> 23:39.931
It was... fine.

23:39.990 --> 23:42.527
We just... watched TV.
Cuddled on the couch.

23:42.528 --> 23:45.865
Twirl was on, so we watched
my brother the superstar.

23:46.863 --> 23:48.941
Heard you boys got into
some trouble last night.

23:51.139 --> 23:52.737
Hey! Hey, hey...

23:52.738 --> 23:55.434
Those boneheads at the
tavern giving you guys guff?

23:55.435 --> 23:58.830
Look, what they don't
understand is that.

23:58.831 --> 24:02.846
Twirl is like the 'October
Sky' of baton twirling movies.

24:02.847 --> 24:04.844
All right? Cheer up.

24:04.845 --> 24:07.442
Hey, Sheriff?
You're gonna want to come and see this.

24:07.443 --> 24:08.641
Copy.

24:08.642 --> 24:09.341
I gotta go, babe.

24:09.342 --> 24:12.219
Okay... see you later. Bye.
I know, sorry.

24:12.518 --> 24:14.936
All right! See you guys!

24:16.614 --> 24:19.849
Well I'm off to go yawn a
big bright chunky rainbow.

24:19.850 --> 24:21.849
I'm gonna... pay the...

24:23.158 --> 24:24.057
What's going on?

24:24.058 --> 24:24.816
Nothing.

24:24.817 --> 24:27.355
What are you not telling me?

24:30.791 --> 24:32.390
No.

24:36.465 --> 24:39.742
You're okay. You just had a little fall.

24:43.718 --> 24:46.194
He's fine... he just rolled off...

24:46.195 --> 24:49.072
I don't know. Looks
pretty scuffed up to me.

24:49.073 --> 24:50.690
Maybe I should just use yours?

24:50.691 --> 24:52.228
No... that's... I...

24:52.229 --> 24:55.247
That's...
Spit it out, special ed!

24:56.066 --> 24:57.123
Nothing?

24:57.124 --> 24:59.422
Well maybe I will use your pencil then.

25:00.741 --> 25:03.297
No! No, please don't... give it back!

25:03.298 --> 25:06.934
No? Don't give you the pencil back?!
Okay, I'll keep it then!

25:06.935 --> 25:09.052
Hey, dipshit's pencil. I'm Chad.

25:09.053 --> 25:11.369
And I'm gonna pay my bill with you
and then snap you in half

25:11.370 --> 25:14.506
to teach your special friend here that
you're just an inanimate fucking pencil!

25:14.507 --> 25:16.106
Chad Cheever?

25:17.005 --> 25:19.401
Quarterback for the
Leechwood Devils...?!

25:19.402 --> 25:20.381
Sup, Paige?

25:20.382 --> 25:22.518
How'd a chick like you wind
up in a family with him?

25:22.519 --> 25:24.116
He's not so bad.

25:24.117 --> 25:27.115
He's got his strengths...
not unlike yourself.

25:27.394 --> 25:29.473
Yeah you're not so bad yourself.

25:30.191 --> 25:33.447
I'm sure we can find something much
better to do with these hands of yours,

25:33.448 --> 25:35.087
don't you think?

25:35.106 --> 25:38.222
What'd you have in mind? Wouldn't
want to piss off the town Sheriff...

25:38.223 --> 25:40.262
That shouldn't be a problem for you.

25:40.841 --> 25:42.859
You're all muscle, right?

25:43.858 --> 25:45.335
And not much else.

25:45.336 --> 25:46.015
What?

25:46.016 --> 25:48.512
You see, Chad... I need
the whole package.

25:48.513 --> 25:53.049
And the word around town is that you
don't have much of a package at all.

25:53.489 --> 25:57.465
So unfortunately for you, it's a...
small town.

25:57.904 --> 25:59.421
What did you say, bitch?!

25:59.422 --> 26:00.760
What did you say to me?!

26:00.761 --> 26:02.258
Your family is such a freakshow!

26:02.259 --> 26:04.216
Hey, you don't know the first
thing about my family, asshole!

26:04.217 --> 26:04.997
Yeah?

26:04.998 --> 26:07.593
Retard... Faggot... and the
princess who thinks she's better

26:07.594 --> 26:10.191
because she happens to be mildly hot!

26:11.210 --> 26:12.248
What is wrong with you people?

26:12.249 --> 26:13.447
Fuck you, Chad!

26:13.448 --> 26:15.366
I might if you ask nicely.

26:18.482 --> 26:20.081
Chad Cheever!

26:21.599 --> 26:23.198
Go Devils!

26:25.136 --> 26:26.593
We're going to State!

26:26.594 --> 26:27.972
God, will you let go of me!?

26:27.973 --> 26:29.990
If I do, will you calm down?

26:29.991 --> 26:31.448
Let's just go.

26:31.449 --> 26:33.947
I can take care of myself.

26:35.485 --> 26:36.963
No you can't, Charlie!

26:36.964 --> 26:38.381
Are you kidding me?

26:38.382 --> 26:40.100
Then I should've just let
them break the pencil

26:40.101 --> 26:42.479
cause then you'd stop
acting like such a...

26:49.831 --> 26:53.248
Say it again! Say it again!

26:53.927 --> 26:55.524
What was I supposed to do?

26:55.525 --> 26:57.302
It's not like Charlie could
do anything about it.

26:57.303 --> 26:59.580
Yes he can, Paige.

26:59.581 --> 27:01.518
You just have to let him try.

27:01.519 --> 27:05.435
I'm the only girl in the world
who has to protect her big brother.

27:07.793 --> 27:09.230
He'll surprise you someday.

27:09.231 --> 27:12.389
Until he does... you better plan on
picking me up from detention.

27:12.428 --> 27:13.648
Every day.

27:17.223 --> 27:20.521
I'm sorry. Charlie, I'm
sorry, I didn't mean...

27:22.338 --> 27:23.937
Charlie!

27:29.891 --> 27:32.129
I feel like I missed something.

27:36.005 --> 27:37.182
Grabeste-Te!

27:37.183 --> 27:39.781
Unde îl îngropam?

27:40.300 --> 27:42.177
Bury?!

27:42.178 --> 27:45.156
No, this traitor we
feed to the wild dogs.

27:48.326 --> 27:52.868
Hahaha! Look! Haha!
Dog is hungry!

27:53.387 --> 27:55.626
Be bones by morning.

27:55.805 --> 27:59.362
Hahaha!

27:59.501 --> 28:04.036
Hey, doggy doggy... you hungry, doggy?

28:04.037 --> 28:08.193
Come on little doggy... time to eat...

28:12.628 --> 28:15.784
Tu Dracul! Strigoi!

28:21.559 --> 28:24.755
Whoa!...what is... that?!

28:24.756 --> 28:27.632
We've ID'ed him. It's that
killer who's been on the loose.

28:27.633 --> 28:31.088
He was just spotted less than
twelve hours ago outside of Leechwood.

28:31.089 --> 28:35.144
Decay around the lacerations show he's
only been dead a couple of hours.

28:35.145 --> 28:36.844
It's his blood...

28:37.004 --> 28:38.042
it's gone.

28:38.043 --> 28:38.862
What do you mean gone?

28:38.863 --> 28:41.558
Completely! Like something
just sucked it out of him!

28:41.559 --> 28:42.797
Like something came along and...

28:42.798 --> 28:44.795
All right, let me stop you
right there, okay, Gil?

28:44.796 --> 28:47.252
It's that kind of talk that causes
pandemonium in this town.

28:47.253 --> 28:50.509
The legends, the stories...
they really freak folks out. All right?

28:50.510 --> 28:53.286
Boys? Mums the word.
Let's keep your lips sealed.

28:53.287 --> 28:55.184
Right, yeah. Yeah, yeah, yeah.

28:55.185 --> 28:56.983
You too, Gil. Okay?

28:56.984 --> 29:00.188
Okay? Got it?

29:04.516 --> 29:05.854
Everything okay, Doc?

29:05.855 --> 29:06.754
Yeah, yeah... I'm fine.

29:06.755 --> 29:10.249
Hey, everyone knows about
the body they found this morning.

29:10.250 --> 29:11.768
I can't talk about it.

29:11.769 --> 29:12.608
Time to take the edge off?

29:12.609 --> 29:16.363
No, no... I'm sober now.
I've been through the 12-Step program...

29:16.364 --> 29:20.401
And here's to step 13.

29:25.656 --> 29:27.892
Something just chewed up his neck!

29:27.893 --> 29:30.109
I've seen animal attacks and this...

29:30.131 --> 29:34.160
No blood... and bitten right here!

29:35.425 --> 29:40.839
It was probably a drive-by! You know,
like one of those gang-bang thingies!

29:40.840 --> 29:42.677
If you're scared I can protect you.

29:42.678 --> 29:45.074
No thanks! Vampires are hot!

29:45.075 --> 29:46.853
Chad, I'm saving myself.

29:46.854 --> 29:50.269
Babe, it's vampires.
We gotta repopulate the Earth.

29:50.270 --> 29:52.947
How many people constitute a mob?

29:55.045 --> 29:57.682
Calm down! Calm down! Calm down!

29:57.683 --> 29:59.474
I'm hearing a lot of rumors...

29:59.474 --> 30:02.317
and any such talk of vampires,
well that's just plain silly!

30:02.318 --> 30:06.654
If there were vampires, those Harkers
would've said something about it, right?

30:08.232 --> 30:10.291
Dadgummit, Denny.

30:16.764 --> 30:18.442
Guys?

30:22.438 --> 30:23.876
Where do they come from?!
Have they been here the whole time?!

30:23.877 --> 30:26.654
How do we stop them?!
What are they, terrorists?

30:27.113 --> 30:30.309
You know, the body the
cops found this morning!

30:30.310 --> 30:31.388
Awful. Tragic.

30:31.389 --> 30:32.647
Always use the buddy system.

30:32.648 --> 30:34.605
Okay, guys! Guys! Please disperse!

30:34.606 --> 30:37.002
Everyone go home...
there's nothing to see here, okay?

30:37.003 --> 30:38.741
These guys don't know shit.

30:41.179 --> 30:42.397
Guys, I am so so sorry.

30:42.398 --> 30:43.556
I don't even know what's going on!

30:43.557 --> 30:45.914
It's okay, honey. We just found
a dead body this morning...

30:45.915 --> 30:49.070
neck was mangled, blood was
drained, had fang marks...

30:49.071 --> 30:50.449
People just get a little paranoid.

30:50.450 --> 30:52.907
See, this is why I was worried
about the whole show thing.

30:52.908 --> 30:56.763
Yeah, of course, vampires!

30:56.764 --> 31:00.159
We know a lot about vampires!

31:00.160 --> 31:02.137
We were just... hey... come back!

31:02.138 --> 31:04.215
Solid, solid police work, Wayne.

31:04.216 --> 31:06.493
Send the whole town over
here to terrorize us!

31:06.494 --> 31:07.212
Good job, pal!

31:07.213 --> 31:08.092
Hey, Ned!

31:08.093 --> 31:12.227
No, no, honey. I am so sorry,
this is completely my fault.

31:12.228 --> 31:14.705
They just hear the word...

31:14.706 --> 31:18.143
and they think of your family.
Let's get inside.

31:25.515 --> 31:27.412
Wayne!
I can't believe I didn't think of it!

31:27.413 --> 31:28.771
How were we supposed to know?

31:28.772 --> 31:32.107
We dumped a dead body with a mutilated
neck drained of blood in the lake!

31:32.108 --> 31:33.806
Well when you say it like that...

31:33.807 --> 31:35.644
I knew it!

31:35.645 --> 31:36.484
Have you been here the...?

31:36.485 --> 31:39.180
The whole time, you sickos!

31:39.181 --> 31:41.378
Mavis, put down the gun! Please!

31:41.379 --> 31:44.894
This here gun is for my protection...
you murderers!

31:44.895 --> 31:47.991
I saw you the other night out my window.

31:47.992 --> 31:49.510
That? We were just...

31:49.511 --> 31:52.827
Get back in here and shut the fuck up!

31:52.828 --> 31:57.162
I know what you did,
I saw it with my own eyes!

31:57.163 --> 31:58.042
Mavis!

31:58.043 --> 31:59.340
Get over there! Both of you!

31:59.341 --> 32:00.300
They're good boys, just like their
daddy. Get over there! Both of you!

32:00.301 --> 32:01.738
They're good boys,
just like their daddy.

32:01.739 --> 32:06.872
These 'good' boys murdered that man
in cold blood and dumped his body!

32:06.873 --> 32:08.870
Mavis, please...

32:08.871 --> 32:12.787
You can all rot in hell...
the whole bunch of ya!

32:12.788 --> 32:14.125
I've had it!

32:14.126 --> 32:19.580
I'm turning you in...
and you Harkers will be done!

32:19.581 --> 32:24.616
You're finished! You're...

32:27.693 --> 32:29.332
Mavis?!

32:34.146 --> 32:35.745
She's dead.

32:36.004 --> 32:38.582
Why does this keep happening?!

32:41.779 --> 32:43.418
Boys...?

32:43.856 --> 32:45.495
We gotta talk.

32:48.072 --> 32:49.590
Well?
I think I'm gonna throw up.

32:49.591 --> 32:51.408
That's the craziest
idea I've ever heard.

32:51.409 --> 32:52.087
Definitely.

32:52.088 --> 32:53.006
I admire his candor.

32:53.007 --> 32:53.865
It would work.

32:53.866 --> 32:54.606
He's right.

32:54.607 --> 32:57.702
Guys, everyone in this town
hates us... we know that.

32:57.703 --> 32:59.600
But for a brief moment, they didn't.

32:59.601 --> 33:01.358
They were interested
in what we had to say.

33:01.359 --> 33:02.896
Which was nothing, apparently.

33:02.897 --> 33:04.455
But what if they did
believe in vampires?!

33:04.456 --> 33:05.095
Exactly.

33:05.096 --> 33:06.713
You don't even believe in vampires.

33:06.714 --> 33:07.792
You're right, I don't.

33:07.793 --> 33:10.629
But I believe people pay
good money to feel safe

33:10.630 --> 33:12.747
and I sure as hell know you
do not want to lose our house!

33:12.748 --> 33:13.367
Charlie?

33:13.368 --> 33:14.745
The probability of your plan's success

33:14.746 --> 33:17.262
isn't high enough to warrant
the desecration of your wife's body.

33:17.263 --> 33:18.461
She tried to kill us, dude!

33:18.462 --> 33:19.981
That's true.

33:21.938 --> 33:23.477
Work shed.

33:33.986 --> 33:34.785
Okay.

33:34.786 --> 33:36.323
I'm not gonna do it! You do it!

33:36.324 --> 33:37.642
You carve things all the time...

33:37.643 --> 33:40.241
I don't carve people with my chainsaw!

33:40.620 --> 33:43.497
I'd love to help you, but...
might get messy.

33:44.696 --> 33:46.295
Help.

33:46.714 --> 33:49.571
Now don't hesitate.
We don't want it to bind up.

33:59.820 --> 34:02.118
It's in my mouth!

34:04.076 --> 34:06.653
Gerry, why are we doing this?!

34:06.654 --> 34:08.411
It's a bad idea!

34:14.945 --> 34:16.724
One down!

34:29.190 --> 34:31.909
Yeah, that'll do it.

34:33.206 --> 34:34.906
Good job, buddy.

34:35.085 --> 34:36.984
I'll get the Shop Vac.

34:37.782 --> 34:40.960
All right, boys.
Here's the plan...

34:41.139 --> 34:44.415
After we lay her outside, I'll draw as
much attention as possible.

34:44.416 --> 34:48.130
You boys go out to the forest
and make yourselves dirty.

34:48.132 --> 34:51.248
I'll call 911 to set things in motion.

34:51.248 --> 34:54.525
And in less than 10 minutes
the news will show up.

34:54.525 --> 34:57.402
So once you see the lights...
make your way back.

34:57.403 --> 34:58.980
Can you tell us what
happened here tonight?

34:58.981 --> 35:02.598
It was a vampire!

35:04.775 --> 35:07.012
Don't worry... I'll make
believers out of all of them.

35:07.013 --> 35:10.369
Those were the ones who saved me!

35:11.449 --> 35:14.944
What was it? What was it?

35:14.945 --> 35:16.083
We chased it!

35:16.084 --> 35:17.043
We staked it!

35:17.044 --> 35:18.501
It got away.

35:18.502 --> 35:20.039
Vampires in Leechwood?

35:20.040 --> 35:22.257
You expect us to believe
this was a real vampire?!

35:22.258 --> 35:24.515
Of course it was a vampire!

35:24.516 --> 35:27.772
We could be dealing with a maniac
on the loose! Where's your proof?

35:29.531 --> 35:32.806
Fine! Fine! You want proof?!
We'll capture it...

35:32.807 --> 35:34.225
and we'll show it to you!

35:34.226 --> 35:37.821
Okay? We're gonna catch the vampire and
you can all see for yourselves! Okay?

35:37.822 --> 35:41.357
Right here! At House Harker! All right?!

35:41.358 --> 35:44.044
You heard it here first, ladies...

35:44.176 --> 35:45.973
Well that wasn't exactly
in the script, Gerry.

35:45.974 --> 35:47.639
It's beginning to feel
now like we drilled

35:47.640 --> 35:49.190
a hole in my wife's
neck for no reason!

35:49.191 --> 35:51.568
I know! I'm sorry... I'm sorry!
I panicked!

35:51.569 --> 35:53.885
Prove it... How are we
going to prove it, Gerry?!

35:53.886 --> 35:56.974
We show them the real vampire skull.

35:56.975 --> 36:00.706
- Where's the real vampire skull?
- I'm sorry, Gerry. We hid it.

36:00.707 --> 36:03.215
From me? Why?!

36:03.216 --> 36:04.853
We're going to lose the house, Charlie!

36:04.854 --> 36:06.791
We had to. I'm sorry.

36:06.792 --> 36:08.769
Your father said that
the skull was cursed.

36:08.770 --> 36:09.769
Wait, you've seen it?

36:09.770 --> 36:13.145
Yeah. I'm no stranger to
the forces of darkness, fellas.

36:13.146 --> 36:16.801
I mean when I first met your pops...
I was still a Priest.

36:16.802 --> 36:20.018
Where do you think I learned on
how to handle the situation with Mavis?

36:20.019 --> 36:23.594
I mean, misdirection of information
is the church's specialty.

36:23.595 --> 36:25.073
Makes sense.

36:25.074 --> 36:26.651
I mean it was ages ago.

36:26.652 --> 36:30.489
But I used to handle exorcisms,
demonic possessions... you name it!

36:46.222 --> 36:50.268
Our Father, who art in Heaven...

